description.narrative: Progress was made towards strengthening systems response structures, including social welfare and justice, during the first 6 months, despite the outbreak of COVID-19 in March 2020 and the subsequent lockdown that significantly increased children's risk of experiencing violence, separation from family and coming into contact with the law. Social Welfare Officers contributed towards case management of cases reported through the helpline and walk-in cases, while the J4C coordinators worked with justice actors to fast track children through the justice system. UNICEF also supported a consultancy to initiate the capacity assessment of UPF and ODPP on GBV/VAC. | Status:No Progress | As-of Date:17/08/2020
